@startuml journey-dev-coverage
' ============================================================
' Developer View: End-to-End Journey x Automated Test Coverage
'
' Same journey backbone as journey-end-to-end, recolored by test coverage so
' the diagram doubles as a Playwright/e2e gap map.
'
'   GREEN  = exercised end-to-end by a Playwright spec (frontend/e2e/*.spec.ts)
'   AMBER  = built, but only unit/component tested (frontend/src/**/*.test.tsx)
'            -> this is the e2e backlog
'   RED    = no automated test (mostly planned / not-yet-built steps)
'   GREY   = backend work, covered by pytest, out of frontend-e2e scope
'
' Coverage sources:
'   frontend/e2e/{reader,library,intake,guardian-console,assignments,profiles}.spec.ts
'   frontend/src/**/*.test.ts(x)  (Vitest component + unit)
' ============================================================

title Developer View: Journey x Test Coverage\n(green = e2e, amber = unit-only [e2e backlog], red = none, grey = backend/pytest)

skinparam defaultFontName "Roboto"
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam roundCorner 10
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #5a3e28
skinparam ArrowFontColor #5a3e28
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #FFFDF8
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #6b6b56
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #f8f3e8
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor #8c6f56
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #F1E9D8
skinparam NoteBorderColor #c9b48f
skinparam swimlaneWidth same

|#F0D9B8|Child|
|#CDDCEC|Guardian|
|#C5D9CC|Admin|
|#E4E4E4|System|

|Guardian|
start
#F6E1B0:Guardian signs in;
note right: AMBER  •  unit: AuthContext.test, ProtectedRoute.test\ne2e covers ONLY the redirect, never a successful login
#F6E1B0:Create child profiles;
note right: AMBER  •  unit: ProfilesPage.test, profilesApi.test\nno e2e

repeat :a new story is wanted;

|Child|
#BFE3C6:Open app, pick avatar;
note right: GREEN  •  e2e: profiles.spec (picker renders / empty)\nunit: ProfilePickerPage.test
#F3C9C4:Tap "I want a new story";
note right: RED  •  planned, not built -> no test
|Guardian|
#F3C9C4:Approve the child's request;
note right: RED  •  planned, not built -> no test

|System|
#E4E4E4:Generate the story;
note right: GREY  •  backend pytest (generation)\noutside frontend e2e scope
#E4E4E4:Safety validation;
note right: GREY  •  backend pytest (validator gate)
|Guardian|
#F6E1B0:"My Requests" -> Generating...;
note right: AMBER  •  unit: IntakePage.test, intakeApi.test\nno e2e

|Admin|
repeat :take the top item;
  #F6E1B0:Open the review queue
  (Flagged / Ready / Processing);
  note right: AMBER  •  unit: ConsolePage.test, FlagBadge.test\ne2e covers ONLY the login redirect (guardian-console.spec)
  #F6E1B0:Review a story
  (flags first, then full text);
  note right: AMBER  •  unit: ReviewDetailPage.test, reviewApi.test\nno e2e
backward:Send back (unit-only, no e2e);
repeat while (Safe for a child?) is (no) not (yes -> approve)
#F6E1B0:Approve  (ADR-005 gate);
note right: AMBER  •  the mandatory safety gate has NO e2e test\nunit only: reviewApi.test, ReviewDetailPage.test

|Guardian|
#BFE3C6:Assign / "Assign more";
note right: GREEN  •  e2e: assignments.spec (sibling add)\nunit: AssignChildrenDialog.test, assignApi.test
|Child|
#F6E1B0:Avatar shows "new story ready!";
note right: AMBER  •  unit: ProfilePickerPage.test\npill state not asserted in e2e

#BFE3C6:Open Library (hero + shelf);
note right: GREEN  •  e2e: library.spec (hero+shelf, tap->reader, empty, mobile)\nunit: LibraryPage.test, pickHero.test
#BFE3C6:Read passages, make choices;
note right: GREEN  •  e2e: reader.spec (play-to-ending US-101,\nstate-gated US-102, malformed->exit, missing->not-found, a11y)
if (Online?) then (yes)
  #BFE3C6:Progress saves;
  note right: GREEN  •  covered within reader.spec happy path
else (offline)
  #BFE3C6:Read from cache, queue progress;
  note right: GREEN  •  e2e: reader.spec (plays to ending, network disabled)\nunit: offline/db.test, offline/sync.test
  #F6E1B0:Reconnect + reconcile a clash;
  note right: AMBER  •  the 409 conflict path has NO e2e\nunit only: reader/dialogs.test, offline/sync.test
endif
#BFE3C6:Reach an ending;
note right: GREEN  •  reader.spec asserts the ending screen
#BFE3C6:Rate a book (library shelf);
note right: GREEN  •  e2e: library.spec (rating posts upsert, fills stars)\nunit: StarRating.test

repeat while (Want another story?) is (yes) not (no)
|Child|
stop

legend bottom
  == Automated test coverage ==
  |= Node |= Meaning |= Where |
  |<back:#BFE3C6> green </back>| End-to-end (Playwright) | frontend/e2e/*.spec.ts |
  |<back:#F6E1B0> amber </back>| Built, unit/component only -> <b>e2e backlog</b> | frontend/src/**/*.test.tsx |
  |<back:#F3C9C4> red </back>| No automated test (mostly not-yet-built) | -- |
  |<back:#E4E4E4> grey </back>| Backend, pytest-covered, out of frontend-e2e scope | tests/ (pytest) |
  <b>Headline gaps:</b> the entire guardian console (sign-in, queue, review, and the
  ADR-005 <b>Approve</b> gate) is amber, plus the reader 409-conflict reconciliation.
  These are shipped features with unit tests but no Playwright coverage.
endlegend

@enduml
